					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-730289#post-1897745</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-730289/a-shift-at-the-factory#post-1897745</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 21 Nov 2013 06:18:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>UglyFlower</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1741178</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>A few issues with grammar, for example the last line uses the word tinny instead of tiny. I wasn't sure if I should change that incase you wanted the word tinny to describe a robot voice or something. A few issues with the way sentences are structured. for example: &quot;Before he could place the torch to metal a hand placed itself on his shoulder.&quot; needs a comma between &quot;metal&quot; and &quot;a&quot;.</p> <p>&quot;A single sentence, spoken in a tinny voice. Something no doubt meant for the dying Manager.&quot; This can easily be one sentence rather than two that sound confusing together.</p> <p>For example it might sound better as, &quot;A tiny voice uttered a single sentence which was undoubtedly directed towards the dying manager&quot;</p> <p>There are more issues similar to these, but I'm too exhausted to go over them right now.</p> <p>Altogether I enjoyed it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
